-- morphism levels before object levels. See note [category_theory universes].
@[simp]
theorem id_hom (X : Core C) : Iso.hom ((«expr𝟙») X) = («expr𝟙») X :=
  rfl
#align id_hom id_hom
comp_hom:
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ⟶ » -/
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ⟶ » -/
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ≫ » -/
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ≫ » -/
@[simp]
theorem comp_hom {X Y Z : Core C} (f : «expr ⟶ » X Y) (g : «expr ⟶ » Y Z) :
    («expr ≫ » f g).hom = «expr ≫ » f.hom g.hom :=
  rfl
#align comp_hom comp_hom
